Reasoning: The paper deals with the mathematical analysis of self-sustainability of energy harvesting systems, which involves concepts from information theory (such as random walk theory), control systems (such as optimal consumption policy), and probability theory (such as Poisson process). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the design and optimization of energy harvesting systems, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with the performance evaluation of energy harvesting systems, which involves concepts from probability theory and stochastic processes, and therefore falls under the sub-category of cs.PF (Performance).
